1. Climate GLMM Analysis

df_model  <- df_alldata %>%
  filter(!is.na(StandardisedAnnualChange )) # Remove NA values
df_modela <- df_model %>% filter (Climate == "Yes")# Extracts the fire-only related rows 
df_model <- df_modela %>% filter(Design == "BACI" | Design == "BA") # Omit CI designs, as this doesn't capture rate of change as t0 is not known. 

df_model$StandardisedAnnualChange <- as.numeric(df_model$StandardisedAnnualChange)
df_model$color <- with(df_model, ifelse(StandardisedAnnualChange > 0, "positive", ifelse(StandardisedAnnualChange < 0, "negative", "zero")))

Assessing whether data differs based on study characteristics: we used the Kruskal-Wallis test to examine whether the annual change in cover-abundance significantly differed between population scales, alpine zones of shrub species and ecosystem types. If p < 0.05, we used Dunns test to undertake pairwise comparisions.

# Population Scale
kruskal.test(StandardisedAnnualChange.2 ~ Response.Level, data = df_model)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  StandardisedAnnualChange.2 by Response.Level
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 7.7965, df = 2, p-value = 0.02028
# Alpine zone of shrub species
kruskal.test(StandardisedAnnualChange.2 ~ Alpine.Zone, data = df_model)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  StandardisedAnnualChange.2 by Alpine.Zone
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 7.3102, df = 3, p-value = 0.06264
# Ecosystem type 
kruskal.test(StandardisedAnnualChange.2 ~ Aggregate.InitialES, data = df_model)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  StandardisedAnnualChange.2 by Aggregate.InitialES
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 16.271, df = 6, p-value = 0.01237
dunnTest(StandardisedAnnualChange.2 ~ Aggregate.InitialES, data = df_model, method="bh")
## Warning: Aggregate.InitialES was coerced to a factor.
## Dunn (1964) Kruskal-Wallis multiple comparison
##   p-values adjusted with the Benjamini-Hochberg method.
##                                                      Comparison          Z
## 1  Cushion heathland / Fjaledmark - Grassland (dry) / Herbfield -0.7213766
## 2              Cushion heathland / Fjaledmark - Heathland (dry) -1.5896211
## 3                 Grassland (dry) / Herbfield - Heathland (dry) -0.9822399
